==English==
===Etymology===
First attested circa [[w:14th century|14th century]], {{ME.}} [[ardaunt]], from {{OF.}} [[ardant]], from {{L.}} [[ardentem]], nominative of [[ardens]], [[present participle]] of [[ardere]], "to [[burn]]."

===Adjective===
'''ardent'''
# full of [[ardour]]; [[fervent]], [[passionate]]
# [[burn]]ing; [[glowing]]; [[shining]]

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[kiihkeä]] (1), [[leimuava]] (2), (3) [[éspanol]]

===Related terms===
*[[ardently]]
*[[ardent spirits]]

